The paper deals with the graph theory aspects of origami patterns, specifically the graphs formed from the vertices and creases of a flat folding pattern. This makes cs.CG (Computational Geometry) the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the connectivity of these graphs, which falls under cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also mentions the degree of vertices, which is a topic in cs.GT (Graph Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of unbounded sheets of paper, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
